main event: Two unidentified flying objects (UFOs) were observed near Lancaster, California on August 22, 1965.
interesting points: The larger object appeared round, while the smaller object was shaped like a flying wing, with no visible empennage.
The larger object initially appeared white but then started flashing lights in a bright/dim cycle as it maneuvered.
The smaller object made an extremely rapid maneuver, crossing over from the left side of the larger object to the right side in an estimated speed over 3,000 mph.
Both objects appeared to increase and decrease in size, suggesting changes in distance, with no apparent lag by the smaller object during its rapid crossover.
The larger object was visible for about 3 minutes, while the smaller object was visible for about 1 minute before disappearing.
witnesses: Civilian observer, a service engineer with General Electric with over 3,000 hours of combined military and private flying experience.
